ng_amount': '', 'notes': '', 'attachments': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}}, {'types': ['Mentoring', 'Awareness', 'Networks'], 'audiences': ['Women'], 'population_focuses': ['Women'], 'campuses': [''], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': ['Rolling'], 'innovation_stages': [''], 'topics': [''], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['WITI'], 'resource': {'title': 'Forté Foundation WOMEN ON BOARDS INITIATIVE', 'url': 'http://www.fortefoundation.org/site/PageServer?pagename=advancement_boards', 'resource_email': 'info@fortefoundation.org', 'resource_phone': '512-535-5157', 'address': '9600 Escarpment, Suite 745 PMB 72  Austin, TX 78749', 'contact_email': '', 'contact': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'It is a surprising statistic, but currently only 17% of Fortune 500 board members are women. Inspired to address this inequity and its impact on the business landscape, Forté partnered with its sponsoring business schools and companies to advance women into corporate board positions.\n\nForté is the only organization in the US that connects the leading business schools and top companies around the topic of women in business. Tapping this network of highly successful women who have corporate board potential will increase access and provide transparency into the selection process.\n\nForté is creating the most comprehensive list of board-ready women with the goal of bringing attention to the lack of women on corporate boards.\n\nForté partners with leading business schools across the globe to identify women who are interested in advancing their careers and ultimately becoming Board eligible. To continue this effort, Forté member schools collectively are making a difference in the number of women on boards by supporting the board ready initiative. \n\nForté has joined forces with the European Commission, the Financial Times and a host of other leading organizations and institutions to play a prominent role in identifying and promoting qualified senior female leadership. Forté Foundation is the US partner of the initiative and a member of the Task Force.\n\nHow to Apply: if you find that your background matches the Forté  Board Readiness criteria, you may be formally considered for the Global Board-Ready Women List. Simply email your LinkedIn profile and the email address where you wish to be contacted. The nominating committee will review your submission and contact you with next steps.', 'fburl': 'https://www.facebook.com/fortefoundation/', 'twitterurl': 'https://twitter.com/fortefoundation', 'insta': 'https://www.instagram.com/fortefoundation/', 'locations': 'Global', 'deadline': '', 'funding_amount': '', 'notes': '', 'attachments': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}}, {'types': ['Networks', 'Training & Support', 'Mentoring'], 'audiences': ['Women'], 'population_focuses': ['Women'], 'campuses': ['Berkeley'], 'colleges': [''], 'availabilities': ['Rolling'], 'innovation_stages': [''], 'topics': [''], 'technologies': [''], 'client_tags': ['WITI'], 'resource': {'title': 'Web Women’s Entrepreneurship in Berkeley', 'url': 'http://www.wberkeley.com/', 'resource_email': '', 'resource_phone': '', 'address': '', 'contact_email': '', 'contact': '', 'contact_phone': '', 'desc': 'Women Entrepreneurs of Berkeley (WEB) is a program of the Berkeley Chamber that works to connect innovative women with the resources and networks they need to accelerate their businesses. In cooperation with UC Berkeley and community partnerships, WEB provides support to women at different stages of their careers and engages women in and around Berkeley.', 'fburl': '', 'twitterurl': '', 'insta': '', 'locations': 'UC Berkeley', 'deadline': '', 'funding_amount': '', 'notes': '', 'attachments': '', 'approval_status': '', 'approved_by': '', 'updated_at': '', 'flagged': '', 'flagged_comment': ''}}, {'types': ['Mentoring', 'Awareness', 'Netwo